HEADWORD: pachouli
<hw>pachouli</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A small East
Indian shrubby mint (<spn>Pogostemon cablin</spn>); a fragrant oil from
its leaves is used in perfumes.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> patchouli, patchouly, <spn>Pogostemon
cablin</spn>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

